version_description: My version of this song is the actual live recording at the "Live From The Mranch".

song_name: All I Want For Christmas Is Us
All I Want For Christmas Is Us

version_description: It's quite simple to play. Jason plays it with a "Dghe"- tuned Ukulele. The strumming pattern is also very easy. Have fun with this beautiful melody.
Version one is good, but it's a live version and it's a little different that this one which is the studio version.

The chords in this tab are absolute, not relative to optional capo (if you were to place one on the 1st fret). This makes it easier to read for those who don't use a capo or, when they do, still see the chords in their standard positions. Ends with a cool F7sus2 chord that Jason often plays live.
Accoring to the live performance at Bonnaroo 2016-06-11.
Uses current lyrics that Jason Mraz uses, based on this youtube video of Jason performing it live and up-close: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sxDc3rAD0Ag.
